org.hps.analysis.util

Class PrintCollectionsUtility

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hps.analysis.util.PrintCollectionsUtility

  • public class PrintCollectionsUtility
extends Object
    PrintCollectionsUtility is a utility designed to print all of the collections in an argument LCIO file from the command line. Users can specify how many events to search for new unique collection names. The utility will print both the names of all collections observed and the object types.

    Additionally, users may specify that the utility should print the full collection data for specific collections. This will only occur if there is a print method for that object type implemented.

      • main

        public static void main(String[] args)
                 throws IOException,
                        NumberFormatException,
                        ConditionsManager.ConditionsNotFoundException
        Iterates over the events in a file and collates all the collection names which occur in any event. Method can also print the data in the collections if a toString(T, int) method (where T is the type of the object) is implemented.
        Parameters:
        args - - The command line arguments.
        Throws:
        IOException - - Should never occur. This is used internally to identify the end of the LCIO input file.
        NumberFormatException - - Occurs if a command line argument that is intended to be numerical is not.
        ConditionsManager.ConditionsNotFoundException - Occurs if the specified conditions set is not found.
